This topic describes how you can delete the Google Cloud Platform (GCP) resources associated
with a <%= vars.ops_manager_first %> deployment.

You can delete the resources in one of following ways:

* If you created a separate project for your <%= vars.ops_manager %> deployment, follow the procedure in [Delete the project](#delete-project).

* If the project that contains your <%= vars.ops_manager %> deployment also contains other resources that you want to preserve, follow the procedure in [Delete <%= vars.ops_manager %> resources](#delete-resources).

## <a id='delete-project'></a> Delete the project

To delete the project for your <%= vars.ops_manager %> deployment:

1. Go to the GCP Console Dashboard.

1. Go to **Project**, and click **Manage project settings**.

1. Click **DELETE PROJECT**.

1. Enter your project ID and click **SHUT DOWN** to confirm.

## <a id='delete-resources'></a> Delete <%= vars.ops_manager %> resources

To delete the resources associated with your <%= vars.ops_manager %> deployment:

1. Go to the GCP Console Dashboard.

1. Click the **upper left** icon and click **Networking**.

1. Click **Load balancing**.

1. Complete the following steps for all load balancers associated with your <%= vars.ops_manager %> deployment:
	1. Click the **trash can** icon next to the load balancer.
	1. In the next dialog, click any **health checks** and **backend services** associated with the
	load balancer.
	1. Click **DELETE LOAD BALANCER AND THE SELECTED RESOURCES**.

1. Click the **upper left** icon and click **Compute Engine**.

1. Complete the following steps for **VM instances**, **Instance groups**, and **Disks:**
	1. Select the check box next to the <%= vars.ops_manager %> resource.
	1. When all <%= vars.ops_manager %> resources are selected, click **DELETE**.
	1. Click **DELETE** again to confirm.

1. Click the **upper left** icon and click **Networking**.

1. Click **External IP addresses**.

1. Select all external IP addresses associated with your <%= vars.ops_manager %> deployment, and
click **RELEASE STATIC ADDRESS**.

1. Click **Networks**, and complete the steps for any networks you created for <%= vars.ops_manager %>:
	1. Click the name of the network.
	1. Click **DELETE NETWORK**.
	1. Click **DELETE** to confirm.

1. Click the **upper left** icon and click **IAM & Admin**.

1. Click the **trash can** icon next to the `bosh` service account you created
for <%= vars.ops_manager %> and click **REMOVE**.

1. Go to **Compute Engine**, then **Metadata**, followed by **SSH Keys**. Delete the `vcap` SSH key that you created
for the project.
